#: dashboard.js:1304
msgid "Additional Protection — DNS Blocklists"
msgstr "Additional Protection — DNS Blocklists"

#: dashboard.js:1305
msgid "Blocks are applied at DNS level on the kids dnsmasq instance only. Updated nightly at 3 AM."
msgstr "Blocks are applied at DNS level on the kids dnsmasq instance only. Updated nightly at 3 AM."

#: dashboard.js:1312
msgid "How this works"
msgstr "How this works"

#: dashboard.js:1313
msgid "Checked lists are downloaded and merged into a single deduplicated file at /etc/dnsmasq.kids.d/dns_blocklist.conf, which the kids dnsmasq instance picks up automatically via its confdir setting. Large HaGeZi lists are automatically substituted with the Light version when router RAM is below 32 MB free. Updates run at 3 AM to avoid peak usage. Each update is syntax-checked before going live; if it fails, the previous list is restored automatically."
msgstr "Checked lists are downloaded and merged into a single deduplicated file at /etc/dnsmasq.kids.d/dns_blocklist.conf, which the kids dnsmasq instance picks up automatically via its confdir setting. Large HaGeZi lists are automatically substituted with the Light version when router RAM is below 32 MB free. Updates run at 3 AM to avoid peak usage. Each update is syntax-checked before going live; if it fails, the previous list is restored automatically."

